tool.name: OpenPepXLLF
tool.description: Tool for protein-protein cross linking with label-free linkers.
tool.command:
@QUOTE_FOO@ @EXT_FOO@ #import re
## Preprocessing mkdir in && ln -s '$in' 'in/${re.sub("[^\w\-_]", "_", $in.element_identifier)}.$gxy2omsext($in.ext)' && mkdir database && ln -s '$database' 'database/${re.sub("[^\w\-_]", "_", $database.element_identifier)}.$gxy2omsext($database.ext)' && #if "out_idXML_FLAG" in str($OPTIONAL_OUTPUTS).split(',') mkdir out_idXML && #end if #if "out_mzIdentML_FLAG" in str($OPTIONAL_OUTPUTS).split(',') mkdir out_mzIdentML && #end if #if "out_xquestxml_FLAG" in str($OPTIONAL_OUTPUTS).split(',') mkdir out_xquestxml && #end if #if "out_xquest_specxml_FLAG" in str($OPTIONAL_OUTPUTS).split(',') mkdir out_xquest_specxml && #end if #if $adv_opts_cond.adv_opts_selector=='advanced': #if $adv_opts_cond.decoy_database: mkdir adv_opts_cond.decoy_database && ln -s '$adv_opts_cond.decoy_database' 'adv_opts_cond.decoy_database/${re.sub("[^\w\-_]", "_", $adv_opts_cond.decoy_database.element_identifier)}.$gxy2omsext($adv_opts_cond.decoy_database.ext)' && #end if #end if
## Main program call
set -o pipefail && @EXECUTABLE@ -write_ctd ./ && python3 '$__tool_directory__/fill_ctd.py' '@EXECUTABLE@.ctd' '$args_json' '$hardcoded_json' && @EXECUTABLE@ -ini @EXECUTABLE@.ctd -in 'in/${re.sub("[^\w\-_]", "_", $in.element_identifier)}.$gxy2omsext($in.ext)' -database 'database/${re.sub("[^\w\-_]", "_", $database.element_identifier)}.$gxy2omsext($database.ext)' #if "out_idXML_FLAG" in str($OPTIONAL_OUTPUTS).split(',') -out_idXML 'out_idXML/output.${gxy2omsext("idxml")}' #end if #if "out_mzIdentML_FLAG" in str($OPTIONAL_OUTPUTS).split(',') -out_mzIdentML 'out_mzIdentML/output.${gxy2omsext("mzid")}' #end if #if "out_xquestxml_FLAG" in str($OPTIONAL_OUTPUTS).split(',') -out_xquestxml 'out_xquestxml/output.${gxy2omsext("xquest.xml")}' #end if #if "out_xquest_specxml_FLAG" in str($OPTIONAL_OUTPUTS).split(',') -out_xquest_specxml 'out_xquest_specxml/output.${gxy2omsext("spec.xml")}' #end if #if $adv_opts_cond.adv_opts_selector=='advanced': #if $adv_opts_cond.decoy_database: -decoy_database 'adv_opts_cond.decoy_database/${re.sub("[^\w\-_]", "_", $adv_opts_cond.decoy_database.element_identifier)}.$gxy2omsext($adv_opts_cond.decoy_database.ext)' #end if #end if #if len(str($OPTIONAL_OUTPUTS).split(',')) == 0 | tee '$stdout' #end if
## Postprocessing #if "out_idXML_FLAG" in str($OPTIONAL_OUTPUTS).split(',') && mv 'out_idXML/output.${gxy2omsext("idxml")}' '$out_idXML' #end if #if "out_mzIdentML_FLAG" in str($OPTIONAL_OUTPUTS).split(',') && mv 'out_mzIdentML/output.${gxy2omsext("mzid")}' '$out_mzIdentML' #end if #if "out_xquestxml_FLAG" in str($OPTIONAL_OUTPUTS).split(',') && mv 'out_xquestxml/output.${gxy2omsext("xquest.xml")}' '$out_xquestxml' #end if #if "out_xquest_specxml_FLAG" in str($OPTIONAL_OUTPUTS).split(',') && mv 'out_xquest_specxml/output.${gxy2omsext("spec.xml")}' '$out_xquest_specxml' #end if #if "ctd_out_FLAG" in $OPTIONAL_OUTPUTS && mv '@EXECUTABLE@.ctd' '$ctd_out' #end if

param.label: Input file containing the spectra
Input file containing the protein database
String that was appended (or prefixed - see 'prefix' flag below) to the accessions in the protein database to indicate decoy proteins
Set to true, if the decoy_string is a prefix of accessions in the protein database
Width of precursor mass tolerance window
Unit of precursor mass tolerance
Minimum precursor charge to be considered
Maximum precursor charge to be considered
Monoisotopic peak correction
param.help: Matches candidates for possible monoisotopic precursor peaks for experimental mass m and given numbers n at masses (m - n * (C13-C12)). These should be ordered from more extreme to less extreme corrections. Numbers later in the list will be preferred in case of ambiguities (space separated list, in order to allow for spaces in list items surround them by single quotes)

param.label: Fragment mass tolerance
Fragment mass tolerance for cross-link ions
Unit of fragment m
Fixed modifications, specified using UniMod (www.unimod.org) terms
Variable modifications, specified using UniMod (www.unimod.org) terms
Maximum number of residues carrying a variable modification per candidate peptide

section.name: peptide
section.title: Settings for digesting proteins into peptides

param.label: Minimum size a peptide must have after digestion to be considered in the search
Number of missed cleavages
The enzyme used for peptide digestion
Comma separated residues, that the first side of a bifunctional cross-linker can attach to
param.help: (space separated list, in order to allow for spaces in list items surround them by single quotes)

param.label: Comma separated residues, that the second side of a bifunctional cross-linker can attach to
param.help: (space separated list, in order to allow for spaces in list items surround them by single quotes)

param.label: Mass of the light cross-linker, linking two residues on one or two peptides
Possible masses of the linker, when attached to only one peptide
param.help: (space separated list, in order to allow for spaces in list items surround them by single quotes)

param.label: Name of the searched cross-link, used to resolve ambiguity of equal masses
Number of top hits reported for each spectrum pai
Set to true, if the input spectra should be deisotoped before any other processing steps
param.help: If set to auto the spectra will be deisotoped, if the fragment mass tolerance is < 0.1 Da or < 100 ppm (0.1 Da at a mass of 1000)

param.label: Use sequence tags (de novo sequencing of short fragments) to filter out candidates before scoring
param.help: This will make the search faster, but can impact the sensitivity positively or negatively, depending on the dataset

param.label: Minimal length of sequence tags to use for filtering candidates
param.help: Longer tags will make the search faster but much less sensitive. Ignored if 'algorithm:use_sequence_tags' is false

section.name: ions
section.title: Ion types to search for in MS/MS spectra

param.label: Search for peaks of b-ions
Search for peaks of y-ions
Search for peaks of a-ions
Search for peaks of x-ions
Search for peaks of c-ions
Search for peaks of z-ions
Search for neutral losses of H2O and H3N
Input file containing the decoy protein database
param.help: Decoys can also be included in the normal database file instead (or additionally) select fasta data sets(s)

param.label: Overrides tool-specific checks
Enables the test mode (needed for internal use only)

param.name: OPTIONAL_OUTPUTS
param.label: Optional outputs
param.option: out_idXML (Results in idXML format (at least one of these output parameters should be set, otherwise you will not have any results))
out_mzIdentML (Results in mzIdentML (.mzid) format (at least one of these output parameters should be set, otherwise you will not have any results))
out_xquestxml (Results in the xquest.xml format (at least one of these output parameters should be set, otherwise you will not have any results))
out_xquest_specxml (Matched spectra in the xQuest .spec.xml format for spectra visualization in the xQuest results manage)

data.name: out_idXML
data.label: ${tool.name} on ${on_string}: out_idXML
data.filter: OPTIONAL_OUTPUTS is not None and "out_idXML_FLAG" in OPTIONAL_OUTPUTS

data.name: out_mzIdentML
data.label: ${tool.name} on ${on_string}: out_mzIdentML
data.filter: OPTIONAL_OUTPUTS is not None and "out_mzIdentML_FLAG" in OPTIONAL_OUTPUTS

data.name: out_xquestxml
data.label: ${tool.name} on ${on_string}: out_xquestxml
data.filter: OPTIONAL_OUTPUTS is not None and "out_xquestxml_FLAG" in OPTIONAL_OUTPUTS

data.name: out_xquest_specxml
data.label: ${tool.name} on ${on_string}: out_xquest_specxml
data.filter: OPTIONAL_OUTPUTS is not None and "out_xquest_specxml_FLAG" in OPTIONAL_OUTPUTS

data.name: ctd_out
data.label: ${tool.name} on ${on_string}: ctd
data.filter: OPTIONAL_OUTPUTS is not None and "ctd_out_FLAG" in OPTIONAL_OUTPUTS

tool.help:
Tool for protein-protein cross linking with label-free linkers.
For more information, visit http://www.openms.de/doxygen/nightly/html/TOPP_OpenPepXLLF.html
